        <headline>Heat Advisory issued June 7 at 1:34PM CDT until June 8 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Temperatures up to 102 expected.

* WHERE...Davis Mountains Foothills and Marfa Plateau.

* WHEN...From 1 PM to 9 PM CDT Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Pets may succumb to the effects of extreme heat. The
elderly, very young, sick, and people with heart conditions are
most at risk in extreme heat.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids even if you don't feel thirsty, but avoid
alcohol and caffeine. Stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on elderly and vulnerable relatives and
neighbors.

Look before you lock! Do not leave young children and pets in
unattended vehicles for even a moment. Car interiors will very
quickly reach lethal temperatures.

Bring pets indoors or ensure that they have shade and cool water to
drink.</instruction>
